headline: Carrier Global (NYSE:CARR) Misses Q4 CY2025 Revenue Estimates
summary: Heating, ventilation, air conditioning, and refrigeration company Carrier Global (NYSE:CARR) missed Wall Street’s revenue expectations in Q4 CY2025, with sales falling 6% year on year to $4.84 billion. Its non-GAAP profit of $0.34 per share was 4.5% below analysts’ consensus estimates.
